com.gmail.alexejkrawez

Class KrawezArrayList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • com.gmail.alexejkrawez.KrawezArrayList<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class KrawezArrayList<E>
extends java.util.AbstractList<E>
implements java.util.List<E>
    Resizable-array implementation of the List interface. Implements optional list operations, and permits all elements, including null. In addition to implementing the List interface, this class provides methods to manipulate the size of the array that is used internally to store the list.

    ! Note that this implementation is not synchronized.

    • Field Detail

      • array

        public java.lang.Object[] array
        The array into which the elements of the KrawezArrayList are stored. The capacity of the KrawezArrayList is the length of this array. When empty KravetsArrayList is initialized, this array is assigned a capacity = DEFAULT_CAPACITY.
